{"word":"H7788 - שׁוּר - shûwr - shoor - Go","slug":"H7788","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שׁוּר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shûwr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shoor"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Go"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E8; - shu&#x0302;r</b> - <i>shoor</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>turn</i>, that is, <i>travel</i> about (as a harlot or a merchant): - go, sing. See also <a href=\"#/H7891\">H7891</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8670\">H8670</a>"}]}